          "function": "Oathbrand as wound kept deliberately fresh, Kaelith awareness of pain without needing to touch"
        },
        {
          "chapter": 5,
          "scene": "SCN-013, SCN-014, SCN-015",
          "imagery": "Brand burns during archive research and Lirien confrontation, described as wound maintained deliberately, tactical suppression weaponized",
          "function": "Oathbrand reframed from punishment to control mechanism — not her self-punishment but institutional containment"
        }
      ],
      "targetDensity": "Present in every chapter 1-10, absent 11-22 after removal. Imagery should emphasize: fresh pain from old verdict, heat that serves no purpose, the brand as both punishment and proof of survival, the collarbone as site of enforced shame."
